ZCZC GE04
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
TUESDAY TO FRIDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 242300 UTC
A MAJOR AND COMPLEX LOW 960 LYING SW OF ICELAND TO START THE PERIOD DOMINATES
THE N ATLANTIC MOV SLWY E THROUGH THE PERIOD AND FLN GRADUALLY. A SECONDARY
LOW CENTRE 980 ALSO LIES NEAR ICELAND. THIS REMAINS CONTAINED WITHIN THE
GENERALLY CYCLONIC FLOW AND MOVS SLWY N AND E INTO THE NORWEGIAN SEA BY THE
END OF THE PERIOD. THROUGHOUT THIS A WEAK RIDGE OF HIGHER PRESSURE REMAINS
DOMINATE OVER CONTINENTAL EUROPE WITH ANTICYCLONE CENTRED TO THE SE OF THE
AZORES. WIDESPREAD STRG WINDS ARE LIKELY ACROSS THE REGION TO START AS FRONTAL
BANDS PUSH S AND E. WINDS PERHAPS OCNL GALE THROUGH THE LATER PART OF TUESDAY
AND INTO WEDNESDAY BUT TENDING TO BE GENERALLY STRG TO NEAR GALE FOR MUCH
OF CULLERCOATS. STRG WINDS EASING IN THE N AND W THROUGH THURSDAY BEFORE
INCR ONCE AGAIN FOR MUCH OF THE AREA BY THE END OF THE PERIOD
